      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "In 2025 that is NOT the correct answer. We don&#39;t want to create a new thread just to express a delegate. Consumer&lt;T&gt; is the closest thing to it. It works -- purists will however find it awkward (on a semantic level!) because Consumer expects side effects to the parameter."
