      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@kape123 The answer is &quot;it depends&quot;. As long as a <code>Runnable</code> object returned by the method exists anywhere, the <code>paramStr</code> will probably not be eligible for garbage collection. It is possible that if the object exists but can never be run again, the JIT (or even javac) may decide to remove it from scope, but we should not rely on such optimizations because they may change in the future."
