      "creation_date" : 1507810503,
      "post_id" : 21460903,
      "comment_id" : 80365023,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I prefer to use constructor with parameter(s)  <code>public RunnableArg(Object... args) {  setArgs(args);  }</code>   then describe local class:  <code>class ActionArg extends RunnableArg { public ActionArg(Object... arg) { super(arg); } @Override public void run() { &#47;* getArgs() and process them *&#47; } }</code>  and use it  <code>Thread t = new Thread(new ActionArg( %param_object(s)% )); t.start();</code>"
