    "last_activity_date" : 1636897146,
    "creation_date" : 1636897146,
    "answer_id" : 69963545,
    "question_id" : 5853167,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Best way so far:</p>\n<pre><code>Consumer&lt;String&gt; oneShot = str -&gt; {\n    \n   somefunc(str);\n    \n};\n\noneShot.accept(&quot;myString&quot;);\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 16272565,
      "reputation" : 157,
      "user_id" : 11750685,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Gyddz.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "dot_cr2",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/11750685/dot-cr2"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : -1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1680695437,
    "creation_date" : 1680695437,
    "answer_id" : 75939066,
    "question_id" : 5853167,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Create a new class that implements Runnable. In this class you can extend the run() method by making abstract methods of your choice.</p>\n<pre><code>public abstract class CCallback implements Runnable {\n@Override\npublic void run() {}\n\npublic abstract void run(Object any);\n\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Now you can use this class as a callback function like this:</p>\n<pre><code>public void whatever(CCallback callback) {\n    String any = &quot;any type of param&quot;;\n    if (callback != null)\n        callback.run(any);\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>&quot;Whatever&quot; method can now finish its task before our runnable runs:</p>\n<pre><code>whatever(new CCallback() {\n    @Override\n    public void run(Object any) {\n        // Here you can reach &quot;any&quot;\n    }\n});\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 9975535,
      "reputation" : 109,
      "user_id" : 7380277,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/hcBRG.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Bernard Agbemadon",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7380277/bernard-agbemadon"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1706295394,
    "creation_date" : 1706295394,
    "answer_id" : 77888468,
    "question_id" : 5853167,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>If the constraints allow it, you can simply do this.</p>\n<p>Method.java</p>\n<pre><code>public interface Method {\n    void run(String msg);\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>Usage:</p>\n<pre><code>private Method mOneShotTask = (str) -&gt; someFunc(str);\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
